an with Vol. 1 No. 1 (May 17, 1902) ; print ceased with in May 18, 1929. Editor: C.C. Goodwin 1902-1918; J.T. Goodwin, 1918- Includes special Christmas issues in illustrated magazine format, 1911-1918. Numbering dropped with August 18, 1917. Vol. 1, No. 1 (May 17, 1902); title from cover (Chronicling America website, viewed Dec. 9, 2020). June 21, 1919 (Chronicling America website, viewed Dec. 9, 2020)."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:30.200Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2020221650/", "image_url": [], "index": 13, "language": ["english"], "location": ["united states", "utah", "salt lake city", "salt lake"], "number": ["2026-04-13t21:30:13", "online resource", "2766-4392", "2020221650", "904431579"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["goodwin's weekly : a thinking paper for thinking people (salt lake city, utah) 1902-1929 [online resource]", "serial and government publications division", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "score": 47.494045, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD F821", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["illustrated works", "newspapers", "salt lake city (utah)", "salt lake city", "utah", "salt lake", "united states", "pictorial works"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T20:59:43.327Z", "title": "Goodwin's weekly : a thinking paper for thinking people", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2020221650/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2020221662/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1890", "dates": ["[1890 TO 9999]"], "description": ["Weekly (Sunday only) Print began with v. 38, no. 115 (Feb. 25, 1890). Publisher varies. Continues the numbering of: Salt Lake daily tribune. Semiweekly ed.: Salt Lake semi-weekly tribune, 1894-1902. Weekly ed.: Salt Lake weekly tribune (Salt Lake City, Utah : 1902), 1902-<>. Other eds.: Salt Lake tribune (Salt Lake City, Utah : Idaho ed.), 1954-1973, and: Salt Lake tribune (Salt Lake City, Utah : Metropolitan ed.), 1960-1972, and: Salt Lake tribune (Salt Lake City, Utah : State ed.), 1954-1974. Vol. 38, no. 129 (March 11, 1890); title from caption (NewspaperARCHIVE.com website, viewed Dec. 15, 2020). Vol. 85, no. 174 (April 5, 1914) (NewspaperARCHIVE website, viewed Dec. 15, 2020)."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:01.189Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2020221662/", "image_url": [], "index": 14, "language": ["english"], "location": ["united states", "utah", "salt lake city", "salt lake"], "number": ["online resource", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "137343114", "2766-3868", "2020221662"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "serial and government publications division", "the salt lake tribune (salt lake city, utah) 1890-current [online resource]"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "score": 47.494045, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["electronic journals", "periodicals", "newspapers", "salt lake city (utah)", "salt lake city", "utah", "salt lake", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T20:59:43.327Z", "title": "The Salt Lake tribune", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2020221662/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2021220348/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1885", "dates": ["[1885 TO 1887]"], "description": ["Daily (except Sun.) Print began with Vol. 1, No. 1 (March 2, 1885). Print ceased with July 16, 1887 issue? Two editions daily: 2:30 P.M. and 4:30 P.M. Not published Aug. 8, 1885. Supplements accompany some issues. Semi-weekly edition also issued: Semi-weekly Democrat (non-extant?). Vol. 1, No. 1 (March 2, 1885); title from caption (Chronicling America's website, viewed May 20, 2021). Vol. V, No. 68 (May 18, 1887) (Chronicling America'